—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2022-09-27-nushell-0_69.mdظ@793c1237fd9f7987e56202c0a63306fb350a82223cc30762fc9fbba72b8a37f7³title: Nushell 0.69‘½ activation changes (kubouch)عô``virtualenv``
To reflect the recent changes to the module environment, we are changing the virtualenv integration to use overlays.

This will come in effect as soon as 
[link: https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/pull/2422] this PR
 gets merged.

In practice, this means that instead of 
``source activate.nu``
, you'll use 
``overlay use activate.nu``
, 
``deactivate``
 will work the same.
Under the hood, calling 
``overlay use activate.nu``
 will activate the 
``activate``
 overlay and 
``deactivate``
 is just an alias for calling 
``overlay hide activate``
.

If you wish, you can manually name the overlay, for example 
``overlay use activate.nu as spam``
, but then you'd need to remove it with 
``overlay hide spam``
 instead of 
``deactivate``
.
’گگع<Title: title: Nushell 0.69
Path:  activation changes (kubouch)
Content:
``virtualenv``
To reflect the recent changes to the module environment, we are changing the virtualenv integration to use overlays.

This will come in effect as soon as 
[link: https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/pull/2422] this PR
 gets merged.

In practice, this means that instead of 
``source activate.nu``
, you'll use 
``overlay use activate.nu``
, 
``deactivate``
 will work the same.
Under the hood, calling 
``overlay use activate.nu``
 will activate the 
``activate``
 overlay and 
``deactivate``
 is just an alias for calling 
``overlay hide activate``
.

If you wish, you can manually name the overlay, for example 
``overlay use activate.nu as spam``
, but then you'd need to remove it with 
``overlay hide spam``
 instead of 
``deactivate``
.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2022-09-27-nushell-0_69.mdظ@babb4f08252ca0e73aa4dc69e328f59275349fe158e9338a8576b73d3c03f067³title: Nushell 0.69‘¼Grammar Experiments (Sophia)عùWe've recently also started working on some improvements to Nushell's syntax. While these aren't part of Nushell 0.69, you can try this experimental syntax in our new 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/grammar] grammar
 repo. Some experiments we're looking into:
Traditional function definition syntax
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
def foo(x: int) { ... }

```
Traditional function call syntax
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
foo(3)

```
And much more. We're hoping to talk more about these experiments as they mature.
’گگع@Title: title: Nushell 0.69
Path: Grammar Experiments (Sophia)
Content:
We've recently also started working on some improvements to Nushell's syntax. While these aren't part of Nushell 0.69, you can try this experimental syntax in our new 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/grammar] grammar
 repo. Some experiments we're looking into:
Traditional function definition syntax
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
def foo(x: int) { ... }

```
Traditional function call syntax
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
foo(3)

```
And much more. We're hoping to talk more about these experiments as they mature.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2022-09-27-nushell-0_69.mdظ@c0f288e4f6c286d4a48b28fdabc1bd68b5628ef24d722c0b87f969b03292d3f0³title: Nushell 0.69‘°Breaking changesعسWe found a regression in the correctness of the 
``-d``
 and 
``-t``
 flags of 
``touch``
. To get the release out, we've removed these flags, but hope to replace them with correct implementations in the future.
We also removed support for duration literals above weeks, including month, year, and decade literals. These were found to be confusing as it's unclear what a duration of a month is (30 days? 31 days?)
The 
``str collect``
 command is now 
``str join``
.
’گگعTitle: title: Nushell 0.69
Path: Breaking changes
Content:
We found a regression in the correctness of the 
``-d``
 and 
``-t``
 flags of 
``touch``
. To get the release out, we've removed these flags, but hope to replace them with correct implementations in the future.
We also removed support for duration literals above weeks, including month, year, and decade literals. These were found to be confusing as it's unclear what a duration of a month is (30 days? 31 days?)
The 
``str collect``
 command is now 
``str join``
.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2022-09-27-nushell-0_69.mdظ@d9cee79fb5e1d40557c5fcfcd82e1ef3bef08abfb5e813bd0c0de903e70d5406³title: Nushell 0.69‘ھNext StepsعھWe've been progressing with our design towards 0.80 as outlined in 
[link: https://kubouch.notion.site/4db276462ba24704919edb4cc4b86be7?v=10506505557f4f7b9a65155128c04250] this Notion page
.
Some time was spent trying out possible new syntax directions but we were not confident to release them yet. In the next release we'll see a removal of features deprecated in this release and we'll continue to push ahead for the 0.80.
’گگعكTitle: title: Nushell 0.69
Path: Next Steps
Content:
We've been progressing with our design towards 0.80 as outlined in 
[link: https://kubouch.notion.site/4db276462ba24704919edb4cc4b86be7?v=10506505557f4f7b9a65155128c04250] this Notion page
.
Some time was spent trying out possible new syntax directions but we were not confident to release them yet. In the next release we'll see a removal of features deprecated in this release and we'll continue to push ahead for the 0.80.
